<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/apple-iphone-air-color-lineup-250909-1757443978292.jpg" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<p id="p2">As usual, today&rsquo;s Apple event was packed with facts, figures, and statistics throughout the presentation and elsewhere. We&rsquo;ve pulled together the highlights.</p>
<p id="p3"><!--more--></p>
<h2 id="iphones">iPhones</h2>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/apple-iphone-17-lineup-250909-1757450265859.jpg" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<h3 id="storage">Storage</h3>
<ul id="ul5"><li>Starting storage is 256&nbsp;GB on all phones announced today.</li>
<li>The iPhone 17 Pro Max supports up to 2TB of storage for the first time.</li>
</ul><h3 id="cameras">Cameras</h3>
<ul id="ul6"><li>All models announced today have 48MP rear cameras and new 18MP Center Stage selfie cameras.</li>
<li>The iPhone 17 Pro line can shoot video in 4K120 fps.</li>
<li>The optical zoom on the iPhone Pro line goes to 8x.</li>
<li>The iPhone 17 Pro Max model gets up to 39 hours of continuous video playback compared to the iPhone 17 Pro&rsquo;s 33</li>
<li>500 billion selfies were taken with iPhones last year.</li>
<li>The CPU is up to 50% faster and the GPU up to 2x faster than its predecessors.</li>
</ul><h3 id="hardware-design">Hardware Design</h3>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/apple-iphone-17-pro-color-lineup-250909-1757450411926.jpg" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<ul id="ul8"><li>The Ceramic Shield 2 on the face of the iPhones is up to 3x more scratch resistant, with the back Ceramic Shield being 4x more crack resistant.</li>
<li>The iPhone 17 Pro line&rsquo;s vapor chamber contributes to 40% better sustained performance.</li>
<li>The aluminum unibody of the iPhone 17 Pro line is more than 20x better than titanium for thermal conductivity.</li>
<li>The iPhone Air is made from 80% recycled titanium.</li>
<li>The new fast charging can take an iPhone Air to a 50% charge in 30 minutes.</li>
<li>Apple&rsquo;s new battery backpack accessory works with just 1 iPhone, the Air, and together with the phone lets users play video for 40 hours straight.</li>
</ul><h2 id="apple-watch">Apple Watch</h2>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/apple-watch-ultra-3-hero-250909-1757458098484.jpg" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<ul id="ul10"><li>The Apple Watch Ultra 3 has up to 42 hours of battery life and 72 hours in Low Power Mode.</li>
<li>The Ultra 3 can charge to up to 80% in 45 minutes and 15 minutes of charging will get you 12 hours of battery life.</li>
<li>You can work out for 20 continuous hours with the Ultra 3. Challenge accepted.</li>
<li>All cellular Apple watches have 5G.</li>
<li>15 minutes of fast charging an Apple Watch Series 11 or SE3 gets you 8 hours of battery life.</li>
<li>The Series 11 battery lasts 24 hours.</li>
<li>The Apple Watch&rsquo;s hypertension detection feature will debut in 150 countries.</li>
</ul><h2 id="airpods-pro-3">AirPods Pro 3</h2>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/apple-airpods-pro-3-hero-250909-1757458196111.png" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<ul id="ul12"><li>65% of the plastic in the AirPods Pro 3 case is made from recycled sources.</li>
<li>Apple says active noise cancellation is 2x better compared to the AirPods Pro 2.</li>
<li>The AirPods Pro 3 are IP57 dust and water resistant.</li>
<li>The AirPods Pro 3 can get up to 8 hours of battery life when using active noise cancellation and 10 hours in Transparency mode with Hearing Aid turned on.</li>
<li>The Ultra Wideband finding via Find My is 1.5x better</li>
</ul><p id="p13"><em>You can follow all of our September 2025 Apple event coverage through our&nbsp;<a href="https://www.macstories.net/tag/september-2025-event/" rel="noopener noreferrer">September 2025 Apple event hub</a>&nbsp;or subscribe to the dedicated&nbsp;<a href="https://www.macstories.net/tag/september-2025-event/feed/" rel="noopener noreferrer">September 2025 Apple event RSS feed</a>.</em></p>
